# Comparison of Four Pillars

| Concept       | Definition                              | Purpose     |
| ------------- | --------------------------------------- | ----------- |
| Encapsulation | Wrapping data and methods together      | Security    |
| Inheritance   | Acquiring properties from another class | Reusability |
| Polymorphism  | One method, many forms                  | Flexibility |
| Abstraction   | Hiding implementation details           | Simplicity  |

