# Exam Definition (5 Marks)

**OOPS (Object-Oriented Programming System)** is a programming methodology that organizes software using classes and objects. It is based on four main concepts: **Encapsulation, Inheritance, Polymorphism, and Abstraction**. These concepts help improve code reusability, security, maintainability, and scalability, making software development more efficient and organized.
